<!doctype html>
<html>
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8">
        <meta content="IE=edge,chrome=1" http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible">
    <title><%= current_page.data.title || "CSV to table" %></title>
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <link href='http://fonts.googleapis.com/css?family=Lato:300' rel='stylesheet' type='text/css'>
    <link href='http://fonts.googleapis.com/css?family=Inconsolata' rel='stylesheet' type='text/css'>
    <%= stylesheet_link_tag "normalize", "all" %>
  </head>
  <body class="<%= page_classes %>">
    <div class="container">
      <header>
        <div class="logo">
          <h1>CSV to table</h1>
        </div>
        <div class="instructions">
          <p>
            <b>Instructions: </b>
            Paste your CSV and play with the options at the bottom of the page.
          </p>
          <p>
            Click on <b>Convert</b> and you'll have your html table ready to go!
          </p>
          <p>
            You can also play with the examples.
          </p>
          <p>Disclaimer: this data is <b>NOT</b> stored</p>
        </div>
      </header>
      <%= yield %>
      <footer>
        <div class="info">
          <p>
            CSV to Table is a tool for converting csv text into tables in HTML code.
            Adds <code>data-title</code> for default in every row to help responsiveness (See
            <a href="http://blog.apps.npr.org/2014/05/09/responsive-data-tables.html">here</a>). You can also read more about this tool in my <a href="http://codingnews.info/post/csv-to-table.html">Blog</a>.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="thanks">
          <p>
            Visit the Github page for this project <a href="https://github.com/malev/csvToHtml">here</a>.
          </p>
          <p>
            Â© Copyright 2014, Marcos Vanetta
          </p>
        </div>
      </footer>
    </div>
